"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-30-Former-Olympians-say-more-needs-to-be-done-for-equality-in-sports-1vEdDQBywrS-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Toni Waterman  Copied  The founding father of the modern Olympics never envisioned the Games including women - famously saying that it would be impractical, uninteresting, and improper.  But through the decades tens of thousands of female athletes have proven that wrong. Now, for the first time in Olympic history, there are nearly as many female athletes participating as there are male. It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a huge achievement, but female athletes see it as only the starting point. Toni Waterman reports from Paris.  For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"